-- Gold Declines, Reversing Gain to Record, as Dollar Climbs; Silver Drops
-- B y   M a t t h e w   O a k l e y
-- 2010-10-06T23:57:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-06/gold-declines-reversing-gain-to-record-as-dollar-climbs-silver-drops.html
Gold dropped 0.2 percent to $1,346.35
an ounce, after earlier climbing to a record for a third
consecutive day, as the dollar strengthened.  Silver also declined, losing 0.2 percent to $23.125 an
ounce after earlier extending gains to the highest since
September 1980.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Matthew Oakley at 
 moakley@bloomberg.net  